  "local_port": 38088,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I distinguish between different ranks of the Indian army?",
  "response": "Distinguishing between different ranks of the Indian Army involves recognizing the badges of rank worn on the uniforms, as well as understanding their hierarchy. Here's a guide to help you identify the ranks, categorized into three main groups: Commissioned Officers, Junior Commissioned Officers, and Other Ranks (Non-Commissioned Officers and Soldiers).\n\n### Commissioned Officers\n1. **Field Marshal**: \n   - Highest rank, rarely awarded.\n   - Distinct insignia: national emblem over a crossed baton and saber in a lotus blossom wreath.\n\n2. **General**:\n   - Four-star rank.\n   - Insignia: National emblem over a crossed baton and saber with a five-pointed star.\n\n3. **Lieutenant General**:\n   - Three-star rank.\n   - Insignia: National emblem over a crossed baton and saber.\n\n4. **Major General**:\n   - Two-star rank.\n   - Insignia: National emblem over a five-pointed star.\n\n5. **Brigadier**:\n   - One-star rank.\n   - Insignia: National emblem over three five-pointed stars in a triangular formation.\n\n6. **Colonel**:\n   - Insignia: National emblem over two five-pointed stars.\n   \n7. **Lieutenant Colonel**:\n   - Insignia: National emblem over one five-pointed star.\n\n8. **Major**:\n   - Insignia: National emblem.\n\n9. **Captain**:\n   - Insignia: Three five-pointed stars.\n\n10. **Lieutenant**:\n    - Insignia: Two five-pointed stars.\n\n### Junior Commissioned Officers (JCOs)\n1. **Subedar Major**:\n   - Insignia: Gold national emblem with a stripe.\n\n2. **Subedar**:\n   - Insignia: Two gold stars with a stripe.\n\n3. **Naib Subedar**:\n   - Insignia: One gold star with a stripe.\n\n### Other Ranks (Non-Commissioned Officers and Soldiers)\n1. **Company Havildar Major/Company Quartermaster Havildar**:\n   - Insignia: Three stripes with an Ashoka lion.\n\n2. **Havildar**:\n   - Insignia: Three chevrons on the arm.\n\n3. **Naik**:\n   - Insignia: Two chevrons on the arm.\n\n4. **Lance Naik**:\n   - Insignia: One chevron on the arm.\n\n5. **Sepoy**:\n   - No insignia for Sepoys, as they are the base level soldiers.\n\n### Notes:\n- The insignia are usually displayed on the shoulder straps of the uniforms, except for junior commissioned officers and non-commissioned officers, where they are often on upper arms.\n- Field Marshal is a ceremonial position and is not part of the active command structure.\n- All ranks wear the national emblem, with the number of stars or other symbols denoting their specific rank.\n\nUnderstanding these distinctions will help you recognize and respect the hierarchy within the Indian Army.",
